---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Can Ocek's multidisciplinary work across technology, business, music, and media."
>
  <header class="page-header container narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Across systems, strategy, and sound</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      I study Management & Technology at the Technical University of Munich and build across
      software, data, business systems, music, photography, and media.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-trajectory-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Trajectory</p>
        <h2 id="about-trajectory-title">Technical and creative foundations</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          My background started with computer science and hands-on technical projects, then widened
          into management, communication, and creative production. I do not see those as separate
          tracks. They are different ways of understanding a system and making it work.
        </p>
        <p>
          I am drawn to work that requires a broad and evolving knowledge base: learning fast,
          recognizing patterns, connecting fields, and turning unclear problems into something that
          can be built, tested, explained, or improved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-work-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Working style</p>
        <h2 id="about-work-title">The useful pattern</h2>
      </div>
      <ul class="meta-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Understand the system</strong>
          <p>
            I try to map the technical, business, human, and creative constraints before choosing a
            solution.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Work through uncertainty</strong>
          <p>
            I set clear goals, test methods, analyze results, and refine the approach when the first
            version is not good enough.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Connect disciplines</strong>
          <p>
            I move between implementation, communication, and production instead of isolating them.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Make ideas usable</strong>
          <p>
            I care about the last step: making the result understandable, presentable, and useful to
            the people who need it.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-range-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Range</p>
        <h2 id="about-range-title">Technical and creative tools</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          My projects have used programming languages such as Java, C#, Python, and R, as well as
          tools for design, media, and production. I have also worked with Arduino and ESP8266-based
          microcontroller projects, including small-scale automation and hardware experiments.
        </p>
        <p>
          The same pattern shows up in music, photography, video editing, audio production, and 3D
          design: I like learning the tool deeply enough to connect it to a real outcome.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-collaboration-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Collaboration</p>
        <h2 id="about-collaboration-title">Clear synthesis</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          I have worked in international and multidisciplinary settings, where the important skill is
          often synthesis: listening to different perspectives, finding the shared structure, and
          explaining the next step clearly.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is the through-line of my work: technical implementation, business thinking, and
          creative production held together by the same habit of learning, structuring, and making
          the result usable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
